# UI theme and role gates

- **Tailwind dark mode:** The project uses `darkMode: 'class'` in `tailwind.config.ts`. The root `<html>` element must keep `className="dark"` so `dark:` utilities are consistent for app chrome. Do not rely on `prefers-color-scheme` for product chrome.
- **Inspector light context:** [`InspectorLightContext`](src/contexts/InspectorLightContext.tsx) forces light-only styling for shared components inside the project inspector. Wrap inspector roots with `InspectorLightProvider`. Shared components that must honor `useInspectorLight()`: `SwipeableCard`, `ChecklistSection`, `CommentThread`, `TaskLinkedAssets`, `ContentLinkedAssets`, `EditableText`, `EditableSelect`, `EditableNumber`. Portals must capture the boolean before `createPortal`.
- **Do not change inspector/panel styling** unless the user explicitly requests it. The `inspector-light` class name alone does not override `dark:` utilities — child components must opt in via context.
- **Project inspector (light surface):** [`InspectorHost`](src/components/workspace/InspectorHost.tsx) and [`InlineProjectView`](src/components/planning-map/InlineProjectView.tsx) use fixed **light** panels (`bg-white`, gray borders/text). Do **not** add `dark:` pairs on those surfaces — they must stay white even when `<html class="dark">`.
- **Global styles:** Do not change [`src/styles/nucleas-tokens.css`](src/styles/nucleas-tokens.css) or [`src/app/globals.css`](src/app/globals.css) unless explicitly requested.
- **Do not branch layout or colors** on `Administrator` vs `Manager`. Use **`isManagerOrAdmin`** (or a specific capability flag) for showing/hiding features. Administrator-only actions may still check `currentUserRole === 'Administrator'` where intentional (e.g. CreateMenu org settings).
- **Stale session:** When resolving the current employee from `/api/auth/me` + employees list, if no row matches, reset manager/admin flags and role to avoid showing the wrong tier of UI.

When adding new surfaces, prefer design tokens and explicit `dark:` pairs that read correctly on dark shells (e.g. workspace `bg-gray-900`).
